                        "@type": "LoreEntryElementType",
                        "id": "01GR6AFCC93PF6T4EYVTXXYJY9",
                        "reference": "INSPIRATION",
                        "subject": "Inspiration"
                    },
                    "text": "The Sandman is a character who appears in many tales and stories for kids. Appearing in Scandinavian folklore as Ole Luk√∏je or Jon Blund, he blows sand into the eyes of sleeping humans to transport them to the world of dreams. When they wake up in the morning, there are often signs that the Sandman has paid them a visit: A sandy crust can be found in the corners of their eyes, which proves he came to lull them to sleep in the dead of night."
